    "body": "## Summary\n\nThe `DeepGemmFusedMoE` branch in `create_moe_backend` (`tensorrt_llm/_torch/modules/fused_moe/create_moe.py`) was silently dropping the `init_load_balancer` parameter, causing **duplicate load-balancer registration** when DeepGemm is wrapped by `ConfigurableMoE`.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`ConfigurableMoE.__init__` passes `init_load_balancer=False` to its inner backend because the outer `ConfigurableMoE` (itself a `FusedMoE` subclass) already registers the layer with the global MoE load balancer. With the parameter missing in the DeepGemm branch, DeepGemm's constructor fell back to the default `True` and re-registered the same `layer_idx`.\n\n### Call chain (before fix)\n\n```\nConfigurableMoE.__init__\n├─ FusedMoE.__init__ (init_load_balancer=True)\n│    └─ _init_load_balancer()  ← registers layer_idx (1st time)\n└─ create_moe_backend(DeepGemmFusedMoE, init_load_balancer=False)\n     └─ DeepGemmFusedMoE(...)  ← init_load_balancer param silently dropped → default True\n         └─ FusedMoE.__init__ (init_load_balancer=True)\n             └─ _init_load_balancer()  ← registers layer_idx AGAIN (duplicate!)\n```\n\n### Audit\n\nI audited every branch in `create_moe_backend` against the target `__init__` signatures:\n\n| Backend | `init_load_balancer` |\n|---------|:---:|\n| TRTLLMGenFusedMoE | forwarded |\n| CutlassFusedMoE | forwarded |\n| CuteDslFusedMoE | forwarded |\n| **DeepGemmFusedMoE** | **missing → fixed** |\n| DenseGEMMFusedMoE | forwarded |\n| WideEPMoE | param not supported (standalone, not wrapped) |\n| VanillaMoE / TritonFusedMoE | not in EPLB whitelist |\n\nDeepGemm is the only outlier.\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] Verify `ConfigurableMoE` wrapping `DeepGemmFusedMoE` with EPLB config no longer double-registers layers\n- [x] Confirm other backends (Cutlass, CuteDsl, DenseGEMM, TRTLLMGen) still work unchanged\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Fixed initialization inconsistency in the DeepGemmFusedMoE backend, ensuring it properly receives load balancing parameters like other Mixture of Experts implementations.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
